questions.text: What is the domain of the function?
questions.solutionText: Domain is the set of x-values.

questions.text: SNOW DAY???  No snow has fallen yet, but Kirkland is predicted to accumulate snow at a rate of 1.5 inches per hour.  Write an equation where S represents total snowfall in inches over t hours.
The distance from Kirkland to Spokane is approximately 279 miles.  It takes you 2 hours to drive the first 124 miles.  At this rate, how long will it take you to get to Spokane?
questions.solutionText: Average speed is 62 miles per hour.  279/62 is equal to 4.5.

questions.text: Find the sum of 17, negative 3 and negative 11.
How many distinct positive factors does 12 have?
questions.solutionText: The distinct positive factors of 12 are 1,2,3,4,6, and 12.

questions.text: A line that includes the point (1,4) has a slope of 3. What is the equation in slope-intercept form?
questions.solutionText: Point-slope formula is one way you could figure out the equation of the line.

questions.text: Big Finn Hill Park has a number of biking trails.  If a park has 48 trails and 25% are designated as expert, how many expert trails are in the park?
An amphicar on Lake Washington can travel 1000 feet in 25 seconds.  Which expression represents the average speed of the amphicar?
questions.solutionText: 1000/25 feet per second is equivalent to 40 feet per second

questions.text: Consider the following graph.  Which statement is true?
choices: The system of equations has exactly one solution.
They are the exact same line.
The system of equations has infinite solutions.
The system of equations has no solution.
questions.solution: The system of equations has no solution.
questions.solutionText: The lines are parallel so they have no points in common.  This systems would have no solution.

questions.text:
Consider the following graph.  The lines are perpendicular.  
True or False:  The slopes of perpendicular lines are negative reciprocals.  Their product is -1.
questions.solutionText: Yes, perpendicular lines have slopes that have opposite signs and they are reciprocals.

questions.text: What is three to the sixth power?
If the slope of a line is 2/3, what is the slope of a line PERPENDICULAR to that line?
questions.solutionText: Perpendicular lines have slopes that are reciprocal and opposite signs.  Their product is equal to negative 1.

questions.text: Kirkland Parks Foundation was established to give the community voice and enable its citizens to raise money for projects that contribute to the Kirkland community.  Simplify the expression \\[ 2(10^{2})*(3^{2}+1^{2})+5(11-8) \\] to see when the Kirkland Parks Foundation was founded.
Find the perimeter.  Simplify.
questions.solutionText: Add up all sides to find the perimeter.  Combine like terms.
